Busy moms, this one's for you! 

Finding those little moments for ourselves can be a challenge, but with Sun-Maid Farmstand Reserve's NEW sophisticated and delicious snacks, you can delight in every bite! #ad

Whether it's during school drop-offs, afternoon pick-ups, or a quiet moment with a good book, these snacks fit perfectly into our daily routines. My favorites? Dried Mixed Berries, Sea Salt Chocolate Coated Banana Chips, Dried Whole Cranberries, and Sea Salt Cocoa & Caramel Dusted Raisins! All of them. LOL! Trust me, you won’t be disappointed!

It's not just a snack; it's a well-deserved break. So why not take your snacking game up a notch with @sunmaid  Farmstand Reserve? You deserve it, mama!

#ad Sun-Maid understands the importance of early literacy and they recently partnered with ABCmouse to make learning fun!
Check out my stories to learn more about all the great work Sun-Maid is doing to help spread a love of learning!

#SunMaid #TurnThePageTuesday #literacy #sightwords #ABCmouse #ImagineThat #Snacking #BackToSchool #LittleFreeLibrary #NationalLiteracyMonth

#ad National Literacy Month 🤝 Snack-tivity • I’m joining @sunmaid to celebrate and support early learning with a fun hands-on activity using Sun-Maid & @abcmouse raisin boxes that feature Fry’s First 100 sight words!

Here’s how: Write the sight words from the raisin boxes on a paper table runner for a matching game. Then, trace the letters with raisins while also enjoying a yummy snack. It’s a playful way to build early literacy skills!

❤️Along with supporting early learning by making snack time fun, for every like on special @sunmaid posts this September, they’ll donate a book to a Little Free Library in honor of National Literacy Month! 📚

#SunMaid #ABCmouse #ImagineThat #Snacking #BackToSchool #NationalLiteracyMonth #turnthepagetuesday

#ad Sun-Maid is committed to supporting early learning by feeding the mind and body! Visit their page and like their posts to make sure every child has a book to read this National Literacy Month! #sunmaid #abcmouse #imaginethat #snacking #backtoschool #nationalliteracymonth #turnthepagetuesday

Celebrate National Literacy Month with @sunmaid!  September is National Literacy Month and Sun-Maid is making early learning fun with special Sun-Maid x ABCmouse limited edition raisin boxes featuring sight words (available at Walmart and select retailers). #sponsored

Sun-Maid has also partnered with Little Free Library to increase book access for children. Throughout the month, they’ll share favorite children’s books on social media, donating a book for every like on these posts.

🚨 VINEYARD UPDATE 

Grapes are continuing to dry through the last stretch of summer-like weather as we head into fall. Growers will be checking moisture to time harvest and boxing of fruit, with optimal moisture percentages. Once boxing is completed, growers will deliver them to the Sun-Maid processing facility to be weighed and inspected. Once inspection is completed raisins are then processed, packed and enjoyed by families around the world! ☀️🍇

One of the greatest unsolved historic mysteries is found in a lake atop a mountain glacier high up in the Indian Himalayas. The skeletons of as many as 800 people are inexplicably in and around the lake. No one knows who they are or what happened to them.

If one of the main reasons you’re hesitant to buy a home is because you’re worried about the upkeep, here’s some information you may find interesting on both new home construction and existing homes (a home that’s been lived in by a previous owner). 

Newly Built Homes Need Less Upfront Maintenance 

If you can afford it, you may find a newly built home could help ease your worries about maintenance costs. Think about it, if everything in the house is brand new, it won’t have the wear and tear you may see in an existing home – and that means it’s less likely to need repairs. Plus, many builders also have warranties on their homes that would cover some of the more major expenses that could pop up.

Existing Homes Can Still Have Great Perks 

But it’s worth mentioning, that it’s not just newly built homes that can have warranties. It’s an option for existing homes too. 

Your agent may be able to help you negotiate with the seller to add one as a concession on your contract. But you should know that not all sellers will be willing to do that. If they won’t, you could purchase one yourself, if you’d like to

If you’re interested in a home warranty for peace of mind, lean on your agent.

So, Should I Buy New or Existing?

While the need for less upfront maintenance is a great perk for new construction, there are some things a newly built home can’t provide that an existing home can. 

Whether you choose a newly built or an existing home, you may be able to ease some of your concerns over maintenance with a home warranty. To weigh your options and go over what’s the top priority for you, talk to the professionals.

If you’re holding out hope that the housing market is going to crash and bring home prices back down, here’s a look at what the data shows. And spoiler alert: that’s not in the cards. Instead, experts say home prices are going to keep going up. 

Today’s market is very different than it was before the housing crash in 2008. Here’s why.

It’s Harder To Get a Loan Now – and That’s Actually a Good Thing

It was much easier to get a home loan during the lead-up to the 2008 housing crisis than it is today. Back then, banks had different lending standards, making it easy for just about anyone to qualify for a home loan or refinance an existing one. 

There Are Far Fewer Homes for Sale Today, so Prices Won’t Crash

Because there were too many homes for sale during the housing crisis (many of which were short sales and foreclosures), that caused home prices to fall dramatically. But today, there’s an inventory shortage – not a surplus. 

People Are Not Using Their Homes as ATMs Like They Did in the Early 2000s

Back in the lead up to the housing crash, many homeowners were borrowing against the equity in their homes to finance new cars, boats, and vacations. So, when prices started to fall, as inventory rose too high, many of those homeowners found themselves underwater. 

But today, homeowners are a lot more cautious. Even though prices have skyrocketed in the past few years, homeowners aren’t tapping into their equity like they did back then. 

While you may be hoping for something that brings prices down, that’s not what the data tells us is going to happen. The most current research clearly shows that today’s market is nothing like it was last time.

Once forced to quit wrestling due to a severe knee injury, Chirag Chikkara spent three years bedridden.

But his passion for the sport never wavered.

Through intense rehab, rigorous physiotherapy, and sheer determination, he rebuilt his strength and focussed on one goal — a stronger comeback.

And he succeeded!

At the U-23 World Championships in Tirana, Albania, Chirag made history as only the second Indian male wrestler to win the U-23 World Champion title.

His victory is more than a medal — it’s a powerful testament to resilience and the unstoppable drive to achieve one’s dreams.

Radha Yadav’s journey from Mumbai’s slums to international cricket is a story of grit and determination.

Hailing from a humble background, her father, Omprakash Yadav, sold milk and vegetables to support the family.

Radha trained with neighbourhood boys using a wooden bat she made herself until coach Praful Naik recognised her talent and offered free training.

When he moved to Baroda, she followed, leaving home to pursue her dream.

Her hard work paid off when she debuted for the Indian Women’s Cricket Team in 2018.

With standout performances in the ICC Women’s T20 World Cup, Radha has become one of India’s top T20 bowlers.

In a touching full-circle moment, she used her first earnings to buy her father a shop — a true testament to grit, family support, and following one’s dreams. 

@radhay21

Rohini Godbole’s passing marks the end of an era in Indian science. The 71-year-old believed that science should be inclusive, and her work reflected that mission.

Her pioneering work, recognised globally, influenced the design of CERN's next-generation particle colliders, leaving a lasting impact on the field of physics.

Her groundbreaking discovery, known as the Drees-Godbole Effect — which explains how photons collide to create new particles — has been pivotal in shaping CERN's particle collider designs.

Awarded the Padma Shri, she dedicated her life to breaking down barriers and making science accessible to all.

Through her book ‘Lilavati's Daughters’ and her contributions to the INSA Report, she amplified the voices of Indian women in science, creating a platform for future generations.

Her legacy continues to shine — a guiding light for those who will follow the path she courageously cleared.

#RohiniGodbole #Trailblazer #STEMChampion #InspiringIndia #PadmaShri #EmpoweringWomen

[Padma Shri, Rohini Godbole, STEM Champion, Physicist, Lilavati's Daughters, CERN]

Manvi Madhu Kashyap’s journey to becoming Bihar’s first transwoman Sub-Inspector is one of resilience and defiance against societal barriers.

Born in rural Banka, Manvi faced rejection from her family and endured financial struggles, initially earning just Rs 30 a day as a newspaper vendor to support her education.

Determined to pursue her dream, she moved to Patna, where she found vital support from transgender activists and mentors who helped her train for the Bihar Police exams.

Her path wasn’t easy — she battled stereotypes, financial hardship, and the weight of being true to herself in a society that often pushed her to hide.

After passing rigorous examinations and being selected among 1,275 candidates, she donned the uniform, becoming the first transgender Sub-Inspector.

Manvi proudly told India Today, “We possess the strength of both men and women." She stands as a beacon of hope for a more inclusive future.

#BiharPolice #TransgenderRights #MadhuKashyap #LGBTQ #LawEnforcement #InspiringIndia
[Bihar transwoman Sub-Inspector, Madhu Kashyap, inclusive police force, transgender police officer, Bihar transgender community, LGBTQ+, gender inclusivity in police, breaking barriers]

"When I was born, my father said, 'My daughter will become a collector,’” recalled Manisha Awhale in an interview with Indian Masterminds.

Manisha’s journey from a farming family in remote Maharashtra to becoming an IAS officer is nothing short of extraordinary.

Despite taunts like, "If you educate your daughter too much, she’ll run away," her father stood firm in his support.

"I come from a society where girls aren’t given the freedom to study, go out, or build careers. They’re expected to marry and settle down. Yet, my father always encouraged me to move forward," she says.

Manisha faced unimaginable challenges. After her prelims, her father fell seriously ill, and shortly after, her mother was diagnosed with breast cancer. Despite these setbacks, she pushed through, driven by her father’s unwavering belief in her potential.

In her first attempt, she cleared the UPSC exam and joined the Indian Railway Accounts Service. But her father, even in his illness, urged her to aim higher. He said, "Go back, prepare again, become an IAS officer."

Fuelled by his words, Manisha returned to Delhi for further preparation and cracked the UPSC CSE 2018 with an impressive AIR 33 in her second attempt, fulfilling both her dream and her father’s vision.

What an inspiring story!
#IASOfficer #UPSC #IASManishaAwhale #WomenInLeadership #InspiringWomen #Maharashtra #BreakingBarriers
[IAS Manisha Awhale, Inspiring Journey, CEO Pune, UPSCCSE, Success Story]

Trigger warning: child sexual abuse

"I was sexually abused from a young age, and I felt isolated and ashamed," Anuja Amin recalls. "I didn't have the words to describe what had happened to me."

Anuja, a 37-year-old survivor of child sexual abuse, is on a mission to empower children and communities to prevent such horrific incidences. Founded in 2015, her organisation, Circles of Safety, aims to destigmatise the topic, educate parents and teachers, and provide a voice for victims across India.

"It takes a village to prevent child sexual abuse," Amin asserts. Inspired by her own painful experiences, she left a comfortable life in the Netherlands to return to India and address the pervasive issue.

Through workshops in schools across the country, she helps parents and educators understand the importance of age-appropriate sex education, including topics like consent, healthy relationships, and personal safety.

“The more I interacted with schools and parents, the more I realised that early intervention is the need of the hour.” she says.

Her workshops have commendably challenged harmful stereotypes and empowered over 9,000 parents and educators and 4,000 children to speak up and seek help.

Read more about her inspiring curriculum that is bringing change in culture: LINK IN BIO.

Shining the light on SAD 💡

Seasonal Affective Disorder (SAD) - also known as the ‘winter depression’ - affects around 1 in 10 people in the UK (it’s a lot less common in Australia ~1%). 

Because it’s linked to reduced sun exposure during the autumn/ winter months, you’ve probably seen advice on social media promoting light therapy as a treatment. But is it legit? 

New research found that when delivered at the right time and dose, light therapy shows meaningful results and may even be one of the best first-line treatment options (this study compared light therapy to talking therapy and medications). 

But keep in mind that this was a relatively small study (~1000 participants), so it’s still worth taking a very individualised approach (looking at diet, talking therapy, medications etc. too). If you’ve been diagnosed with SAD and had your vitamin D and thyroid levels checked, it could be worth trialling the approach below for a few weeks and reporting the results back to your GP/ family physician. 

If you’re struggling with SAD or know someone who is, here are my takehomes...
💡Look for a light box that produces 10,000 lux of light. Plus, check that it’s made specifically for SAD (you can get light boxes for different things like skin therapy, for example) and has very little UV light. Use it for 30 minutes within your first waking hour (aiming for an exposure of around 5,000 lux per day). 
🍴Try eating a handful of pistachios an hour before bed. They’re a valuable source of magnesium and vitamin B6 + contain melatonin, the hormone that supports your sleep-wake cycle. Full disclosure: the amount of melatonin you absorb into your blood might not be significant enough to make a huge difference for everyone, but it’s worth trialling in my experience.
🐟 Across the week, aim for two servings of oily fish (think salmon, sardines, herring, mackerel) for those essential omega-3s. Or, if you don’t eat fish, consider taking algae oil supplements instead.

Don’t forget to share this with someone who might need it ✅

My ‘more than 2’ rule for ultra-processed foods (UPF)... 🤯

We can’t escape UPF; this is an ongoing hot topic, and for good reason! Did you know that UPF currently makes up: 
🍟 Over two-thirds of the average UK teenager’s daily calories 
🍟 Nearly half of a UK toddler’s daily intake 
🍟 About 50% of total energy intake across the UK

Now, not all UPF is non-nutritious (more on that soon!), and I’m a firm believer in inclusion, not exclusion, so cutting out UPF completely isn’t the answer, IMO. But these numbers are eye-opening, and there are growing numbers of studies linking some UPFs with increased risks of conditions like inflammatory bowel disease, type 2 diabetes, etc.

The tricky part? We’re not yet sure what component of UPF could be the issue. That’s why our team at King’s College London is delving into the effects of certain food additives, such as emulsifiers—commonly found in UPF—on gut health. I’ll keep you updated as our research unfolds.

As I said in the clip from my @itvxofficial episode you really don’t need to spend all your time analysing packets, doing more home cooking is the simple answer. 

But if you’re keen to get more savvy at the supermarket, here is my suggestion:
✅ Become your own food detective and check the back of the pack. If a food contains more than 2 ingredients that you’re unlikely to add if you were to make that food at home e.g. sugar and palm oil in your bread, or there are more than 2 things in the ingredients list that you don’t recognise, then it could be worth checking for another brand, or making your own.
✅ My rule of ‘more than 2’ exists because many packaged foods will contain a preservative in them.  Many of these are unfamiliar in your kitchen and can sound intimidating, but they’re generally fine. For example, you might see ascorbic acid added to sauces, which is actually just vitamin C, and calcium propionate added to pitta bread, which is naturally found in certain cheeses.

Too good to be true? 🩸

Hormone-hacking is all over social media, and this is one trend I can get behind for period health. From painful to heavy periods, the experience can be exhausting, but the good news? Tapping into the gut:hormone connection may offer some relief.

A 2024 study found that women who regularly ate carotenoid-rich plant foods (think colourful fruits and veggies) were around 40% less likely to experience painful periods compared to those who didn’t. Another study linked low fruit intake to greater period pain, with women eating less than two pieces a day being three times more likely to suffer. And if heavy periods are the issue, daily olive oil intake was also linked to a lighter flow. (I take mine with sourdough – simple but effective!)

Here’s how to put the science into action👇

🍴 Keep whole fruit on your menu! No need to cut these out over ‘sugar’ fears – they’re hormone-balancing powerhouses. Frozen mixed fruit bags are a great option to boost intake (and gut-loving diversity!) easily.
🍴 Embrace healthy fats. Fat doesn’t make you fat; it’s essential for hormone health. Top porridge with nuts and seeds, drizzle extra virgin olive oil on salads, or enjoy a salmon fillet with roasted veg for that hearty dose.
🍴 Amp up carotenoid-rich veggies, especially the week before your period. Think pumpkin, carrots, squash, and sweet potato – or fruits like mango and papaya.

Share this with anyone who needs a little gut:hormone guidance!

Proof you can have both, naturally 🎃 

While many people prioritise upping their protein, I’m more concerned that most aren’t reaching their recommended 30g of fibre per day (the average is 20g). With fibre being our gut’s favourite food, and the link between our gut microbes and muscle mass, you’ll know why I think it’s so important to up this number.

But with my pumpkin soup recipe, you really can have both, with over 20g of protein, 10g of fibre and 9 plant points per serving. 

Ingredients (serves 4) 👩‍🍳
1 red pepper, roughly chopped
1 large tomato, roughly chopped
1 red onion, roughly chopped
1kg pumpkin, roughly chopped
1 bulb of garlic, top chopped off 
2tsp cumin 
½ tsp of ground black pepper 
2tbsps of extra virgin olive oil 
500ml of vegetable stock
350g silken tofu
Sea salt, to taste

Optional toppings:
Chickpeas, roasted (approx 60g cooked per serve)
Handful of parsley, chopped 
Handful of mixed seeds (5g per serve)
Plain yoghurt (I used @bioandmeuk kefir yoghurt ) (approx 75g per serve)
Feta, crumbled (approx 30g per serve)

Method
1️⃣ Preheat your oven to 200°C.
2️⃣ Place the red pepper, tomato, onion, squash and the bulb of garlic in a baking tray, rubbing in the cumin, sea salt, black pepper, olive oil and then place in the oven for 30 minutes.
3️⃣ Once everything is thoroughly cooked, remove from the oven and leave to cool for a few minutes, then add everything to the blender (squeezing the garlic out of their shells) along with the vegetable stock and tofu and blend for 1-2 mins until smooth.
4️⃣Serve with your toppings of choice. 

Hit save for a perfect cosy Autumn evening 🍂

Liquid gold...or is it? 🫒

It’s a Mediterranean diet staple, but you might be surprised to hear that not all extra virgin olive oil (EVOO) you see on your supermarket shelves is made equal. 

Unfortunately, it’s a poorly regulated market, which is why low-quality (and even fraudster) “EVOOs” are constantly slipping through the net. So while you may think you’re making the best choice for you and your microbes, you might not actually be getting the gut-loving EVOO properties shown in clinical trials.

It’s a huge bugbear of mine so here are 5 things you should be checking…

🫒 The ‘extra-virgin’ label - means it’s minimally processed (compared to standard olive oil eg. “pure olive oil,” “lite/light olive oil,” and “pomace olive oil”) and in turn, is higher in polyphenols. It’s this component that has been linked with everything, from immune support to heart health, thanks to your gut’s connections. 

🫒 The harvest date - EVOO isn’t like a fine wine; it doesn’t get better with age. Look for a harvest date within the last year and a best-before date well into the future so you know you’re getting a fresher oil.

🫒 Polyphenol content - some oils will actually include the total polyphenol/ phenol content (the compounds that are studied for their health benefits) on their nutritional information panels. A phenol count above 220 is considered high but some EVOOs will contain 350+! 

🫒 Darker glass bottles (or tins) - the gut-nourishing polyphenols in EVOO start to degrade when they’re exposed to light, heat and oxygen during storage. Buying EVOO that’s in a dark, glass bottle (or tin) and keeping away from heat helps to prevent this, keeping your oil fresher for longer.

🫒 Independent certifications - national and international certifications are a great marker of quality and guarantee your pick isn’t an EVOO fraudster.

Save this checklist for your next supermarket visit ✅

The change you didn’t see coming 🫠

Just when it already feels like menopause is tough enough with symptoms like night sweats and hot flashes affecting most women, research is now looking at its effects on gut health too.

One 2022 study featuring 2,300 participants found that postmenopausal women had lower gut microbiome diversity compared to pre-menopausal women, whereas there were no major differences between younger men and older men (oh the joys of being female!). It doesn’t end there. A 2020 study showed that symptoms of IBS tended to be worse post-menopause than pre-menopause, with the drop in oestrogen and progesterone levels likely to explain at least in part the higher levels of symptoms like bloating, gas and distention. 

But there is some good news - hacking our microbiome can make a measurable difference.

Here’s what you can do (based on clinical trials and what I’ve seen work in clinic)👇

🦠 Over the next three months, gradually increase your vegetable intake to 5x servings, and fruit to 2x servings per day. 1x serving veg = 1/2 cup cooked veg or 1 cup salad. 1x serving fruit = 80g fresh or 30g dried. Check out my recipe hub for plenty of easy hacks, like grating carrots in your porridge.
🦠 Include cooked soybeans (aka edamame beans) daily (½ cup/ 86 g).
🦠 Switch out butter for olive oil and deep-fried food for baked or air-fried (of course, it’s still fine to occasionally have both if you love them).
🦠 Try to get into a habit of having your last meal of the day 4 hours before bed. 
🦠 For those struggling with IBS-related symptoms, halve the fruit, veg and soybean target. More tips for you coming soon.

Another reason to feed your microbes...🧠

Dementia is likely to affect someone in your family, with the shocking reality that over 982,000 people are living with Dementia in the UK alone. It was the leading cause of death in 2022 😥 

While there are risk factors at play that we can’t control (like genetics, gender and age), there is growing evidence to suggest that a diet rich in polyphenols, folate, omega-3 fatty acids, and β-carotene, can help override some of these factors and reduce your risk of dementia through the gut:brain connection. 

Put the science into action by adding these 4 things to your shopping basket this week and let’s empower ourselves by focusing on the factors that are in our control👆

Takehome...
🧠 While these foods are recommended, diets high in certain types of saturated fats (think fat in steak, skin on chicken, butter etc.) and alcohol might have the opposite effect. I’m all about INclusion vs EXclusion, but be mindful about your intake of these, especially if you are at higher risk of developing dementia. 
🧠 Give your microbes a helping hand by doing regular exercise too. Those who engage in regular physical activity have a reduced risk of developing the disease, so make sure you’re getting your heart rate up for at least 30 minutes at least three times a week.

Pumpkin spice and the not-so-nice…🎃

Check the bottom of the caption for my super easy prebiotic-packed frothy latte recipe 👇 

Your favourite coffee shop’s seasonal drinks are everywhere right now. But what many don’t realise is they can contain anywhere between 25g to 40g of ADDED sugar in a medium cup (that’s around 6-8 sugar sachets!) 🤯 

Now, despite what social media will have you believe, sugar isn’t actually ‘toxic’ for your microbes... 

...but we know indirectly if you’re filling up on these instead of feeding your microbes the foods they love, your gut health will take a hit. And knowing that those microbes impact everything from your immune system to mental health it’s worth considering how much you lean into these drinks (particularly important during cold and flu season, or for those suffering from Seasonal Affectiveness Disorder SAD).

Of course, you don’t need to give them up altogether (I know for many, they do offer nostalgia, marking the start of the autumn/ festive season!). But if you want a gut-nourishing alternative that’s going to satisfy your microbes and your sweet tooth, give my frothy cashew latte a try from my second book, Eat More, Live Well. 

All you need is:
1 cup of hot coffee (approx 250ml)
30g roasted cashew nuts 
1 Medjool date

Just put all the ingredients in a blender (ideally 1000W) and blitz for a minute or two until smooth and frothy on top. 

Save for later or share with a friend for their next coffee fix ☕

There are so many decisions with product creation— first you want to find formulas that work, that are effective at what they need to do… That fit into a price point that you need to fit into them …and that people actually want to try them.

there are ingredient decisions, packaging, decisions, marketing decisions… All the things. And it is so fun to put together the pieces to bring a product out that solves a problem, and is effective and affordable… Not to mention on brand and aesthetic. 

A lot of times we launch with what we have! But when there is an opportunity to improve a product, we definitely take that into consideration. Obviously changing packaging or even labels, can be confusing and even expensive so we want to make sure it’s worth it. 

With our deodorant, when these containers became available we realized that it was worth switching to them. They get stuck less easily, and I feel like they make application so much smoother. They were worth the troubles :-) 

As you can see we went through a lot of iterations for how to switch the label and still make a black container. Look like THE YELLOW BIRD for our lighter and brighter aesthetic. I think one of the best parts of this job is that you never get bored doing the same thing over and over lol.

Did you know that antibacterial soap can actually be harmful for your skin? 

Yes, it still gets your hands clean. But they frequently kill the healthy bacteria your skin and body needs. Antibacterial soap doesn’t discriminate, so it can destroy the healthy biome of bacteria your skin works hard to products. Traditional soap has been shown to be just as effective! 

Plus, antibacterial soap contains synthetic chemicals which are definitely not good for your skin. 

At the end of the day, the FDA has ruled that there is insufficient evidence that antibacterial soaps are more effective at killing harmful germs than traditional soaps.If you are looking for a natural, effective, and safe soap for yourself and your family, traditional soaps remain the best option. 

#antibacterialsoap #soap #naturalsoap #naturalsoapbars #naturalskincareproducts #organicskincare #organicskincareproducts #ditchtheplastic #readthelabel

Hidden veggies mac & cheese?? YES PLEASE 🤩 Recipe below ⬇️

// INGREDIENTS //
2 boxes Thrive Market Organic Chickpea Pasta Shells
1 cup cashews, chopped
½ cup carrots
½ cup russet potatoes, peeled & chopped
1 tsp smoked paprika 
1 tsp onion powder
1 tsp garlic powder
1 tsp salt
½ tsp pepper
½ tsp turmeric
⅓ cup nutritional yeast
1 cup plant-based milk
½ cup plant-based cheese, shredded
2-3 tbsp lemon juice
½ cup panko bread crumbs

// INSTRUCTIONS //
• Preheat the oven to 400 F. Bring a large pot of water to a boil. Add in cashews, carrots, and russet potatoes and let boil until all ingredients are soft (5-10 minutes). Add the boiled ingredients into a large blender, along with smoked paprika, onion powder, garlic powder, salt, pepper, turmeric, nutritional yeast, plant-based milk, plant-based cheese, and lemon juice. Blend until smooth. 
• Bring a medium pot of water to a boil. Add in shells and cook per packaging instructions. Strain and add to a 9x13-inch glass baking dish. 
• Coat the cooked pasta noodles with the cheese sauce and top with your choice of breadcrumbs. Bake for 10 minutes or until breadcrumbs are golden brown. Remove from the oven.

Add all the ingredients for the vinaigrette into a blender and blend until smooth and creamy. Set aside for serving.

Pre-cooked shredded beef > Defrosting frozen beef. Comment below with your favorite time-saving meal hacks! 

// INGREDIENTS //
• @thrivemarket Grain-Free Taco Shells 
• 1 white onion
• 2 packets @wildplanet Organic Shredded Beef 
• ½ tbsp chili powder 
• 2 tsp cumin powder
• ¼ tsp cayenne pepper 
• Salt & pepper to taste
• 1 lime
• ¼ cup cilantro 
• Toppings: Cheese and shredded red cabbage

// METHOD //
Heat the taco shells according to the directions on the package. 
Slice one half of the white onion, making sure to set aside the other half for topping. 
In a large skillet, heat 2 tbsp of neutral oil over medium heat. 
Add the sliced white onions, and sauté until translucent. 
Mix in the shredded beef, chili powder, cumin, cayenne, salt, and pepper, then cook until the meat begins to brown. 
Chop the cilantro and remaining half onion, then add into a small bowl. 
Squeeze lime juice, mix well, and set aside. 
Spoon the shredded beef mixture into the taco shells, then top with cheese, shredded cabbage, and the onion-cilantro mixture.

What is FKS?
FKS stands for functional keratin serum.
The Bioactive technology contained in FKS helps repair, rescue, renew and protect hair. FKS has the unique ability to actually restructure the hair by imbedding proteins into the hair, providing a permanent conditioning service. This product intelligently repairs the damaged areas of the hair, eliminating frizz, giving shine and health to the hair. To use FKS for a permanent conditioning service, the hair must be in reduced state (such as during a chemical service).
.

With these words, a burning desire to learn and an optimistic worldview, Sara Spencer Washington harnessed the power of her femininity to become one of the first Black woman millionaires. She built a beauty empire of products, schools, publishing houses and pharmaceuticals that endured the Great Depression and racial segregation in Atlantic City, NJ.

Madam C. J. Walker (1867-1919) was “the first Black woman millionaire in America” and made her fortune thanks to her homemade line of hair care products for Black women. Born Sarah Breedlove to parents who had been enslaved, she was inspired to create her hair products after an experience with hair loss, which led to the creation of the “Walker system” of hair care.

Delhi Air Quality Index (AQI) continues to deteriorate as it crossed the 400 mark on Sunday, two days after Diwali. The air pollution level now lies in the alarming ‘hazardous’ category in the national capital as of 10:30 am, which is detrimental to the health of people living in Delhi and its adjoining areas.

A thick layer of smog engulfed the national capital, and the AQI was recorded above 300 in most areas, making Delhi-NCR’s PM2.5 levels over 50 times more threatening than the WHO-prescribed limit, according to the AQICN data.

An AQI, which is a report of the quality of air in a region, is considered ‘poor’ between 200-300, ‘very poor’ at 301 and 400, severe at 401 and 450 and above 450 is “severe-plus” and can cause damaging health concerns to residents.

Hi UpCirclers, co founders Anna and Will here. We wanted to use today’s post to give a massive shout out to the thousands and thousands of you that took part in our recent customer survey and to let you know what we’ve learnt from your answers. Your insights really do play a massive role in shaping the future of our brand and we’ve enjoyed unpacking the recurring themes.

The main things we’ve already begun working on are:

✅ We’ve already streamlined our bundles, reducing the number bundles and number of products per bundle in order to lower the price of each one.
✅ We’ve been working on some of the products you’d like to see next for over a year! THIS MONTH we have two launches, with more not long after, so keep your eyes peeled!
✅ We’re looking at options for changing how our refill scheme operates. This certainly feels like a “no right answer” problem, but our priorities in the solution we choose will be sustainability and something that we can launch globally, not just in the UK.

Once again, we can’t thank you enough for taking the time to complete the survey. We’re very proud of the community we’ve created so thank you for being a part of it and believing that circular skincare is the future!

If you ever have more thoughts, ideas, or suggestions, we’re all ears so please pop them in the comments or send us a DM. We thrive on your input, and together, we’ll continue making our brand even more incredible. ❤️

Anna & Will

We know our shampoo crème is a little different to what you’re used to. Its concentrated formula means that the typical dose is significantly less than what you’d have to use with a traditional liquid shampoo. But how does this differ with different hair types and different hair lengths. This is in fact the most commonly asked question about our shampoo at the moment. Whilst this isn’t an EXACT science, it’s certainly a helpful guide.
 Most people when washing their hair do not spend sufficient time wetting the hair and scalp before applying product. If you take at least 1-2 minutes to ensure the hair is really wet (scalp massage can also be incorporated at this stage) then product that you use, will more effective. Your shampoo crème for example will spread across the hair and lather more evenly and efficiently if the hair is really wet. This can also mean that you need slightly less product.

I had Like A Prayer stuck in my head for the 3rd Deadpool film since 2017. Before Wolverine entered the chat, It was largely gonna be the same motion-control sequence I’d been dreaming about, except my dance partner was originally COLOSSUS. He would have died in the preceding scene, launching Deadpool into a state of pure rage and revenge… all set to @madonna’s inspired and singular song, Like A Prayer. 

Obviously, Hugh joining changed the destiny for everyone. (And Colossus, along with his virginity, stayed intact) 

The whole movie lives and dies on partnerships. My partnership with @slevydirect is one that I’ll never take for granted. I can’t live without him. My partnership with @thehughjackman and the trust and history between all three of us is the glue. 

But so much storytelling springs out of composer, @rob_simonsen. And one of his biggest challenges was the choral reprisal of Like A Prayer.  We’d always planned a reprisal, but thought we’d be using stems from the original recording. Then, with a massive assist from Madonna, it became so much more.

Rob is an actual genius. That isn’t even a compliment. It’s just a fact. Part of the job is to make it all look easy — but the engine behind Rob’s genius is a willingness to sit in a problem for long periods of time. He sat in the uncomfortable feeling of not knowing. I wouldn’t be surprised to find out he’s STILL working on the film. He lit the path ahead and this sequence became our favourite piece of the whole film. 

And NONE of this works without the Heavenly Voices Choir of South LA and London Contemporary Orchestra. They are giants of talent. 🙏

*film nerds: In Lawrence of Arabia, David Lean set almost all the movement in frame from left to right to emphasize the journey. I’m not suggesting there’s any common denominator between LoA and D&W. Just that years ago, @TCM did a piece on Lean. I digested and swallowed this little “left to right” chestnut without bothering to chew. Now I can’t look at a frame moving right to left without baselessly disliking it. Obviously David Lean was a brilliant, peerless man. But if he were alive today, my glove to his damned insolent cheek!
Took this whole “Hold my beer” thing to its logical conclusion. Welcome to Wrexham Lager.
Two years ago. A smidge of writer’s block. And I guess that all worked out pretty well. #TilYoure90

Quincy Jones, the wunderkind turned producing powerhouse who shaped American song (and countless careers), has died. He was 91. 

"He was a producer, composer, arranger, instrumentalist, impresario, author, mentor, magazine founder," writes Mark Rozzo." Along the way, Jones might have rarely been center stage, but he imbued a head-spinning variety of musical genres—jazz, pop, R&B, easy listening—with sparkle and sophistication, all while shaping the creative trajectories of some of the titans of recorded music, among them Frank Sinatra, Ray Charles, and Michael Jackson."

There’s still not a lot that #Yellowjackets cocreator Ashley Lyle can say about the third season of her Emmy-nominated drama series, but she does want to make one thing clear: Answers are coming.

The show has now cleared the lanes in both the past and present—with Shauna, Van, Taissa, and Misty tenuously reunited—for a fresh start. At the same time, long-standing mysteries regarding what happened in the wilderness, the fates of certain characters, and the lingering question of how (or if) supernatural forces factor into the show’s events may at last be resolved.

“We are going to learn more about what happened in the wilderness that they are so afraid of coming out,” says Lyle. “We hope it will be both satisfying and at times unexpected.”

Everything. Is. Terrible. 
Or so you might think, if you are doomscrolling right now. 

Coined around 2020 during the COVID-19 pandemic, doomscrolling refers to the act of spending excessive time reading large amounts of negative news online.

Studies suggest that doomscrolling can affect anyone, but is particularly prevalent among youth. In 2019, a study by the National Academy of Sciences found that excessive consumption of negative news can be linked to a decline in mental and physical health.

So, why do we doomscroll?

😡 Negativity Bias: Humans have a natural tendency to focus more on negative information. This bias may stem from evolutionary survival mechanisms, where being alert to dangers was crucial. 

😰 Fear of Missing Out (FOMO): The anxiety of missing important news can drive people to continuously check for updates, even if it negatively impacts their well-being. Studies have found that a significant percentage of social media users experience FOMO, leading them to engage more with online content.

📱 Technology: The design of social media platforms can exacerbate doomscrolling. Features like the “infinite scroll” allow users to continuously view content without natural stopping points, making it easier to lose track of time and continue consuming negative news.

Doomscrolling can lead to beliefs similar to the “mean world syndrome” identified in the 1970s. This term describes the false view that the world is more dangerous than it actually is, due to prolonged exposure to violence-related content on television. Studies show that consuming upsetting news encourages individuals to seek out even more negative information, creating a self-perpetuating cycle. This can distort our perception of reality, making the world seem overwhelmingly negative. 

Instead of doomscrolling, why not go down a Wikipedia rabbit hole? It may be healthier than looking at the next post in your feed. Read more about doomscrolling at the link in our bio.

#Doomscrolling #Wikipedia

🎃✨ Unveil the ancient festival that inspired modern Halloween.

Samhain is a Gaelic festival marking the end of the harvest season and the beginning of winter that is celebrated from sunset on 31 October to sunset on 1 November.

Originating over 2,000 years ago among the Celtic people, Samhain is considered a time when the veil between the physical world and the spirit world is at its thinnest.

During Samhain, communities gather to light bonfires, offer sacrifices of crops and animals, and wear costumes and masks to ward off harmful spirits. These traditions were meant to protect families and livestock during the harsh winter months and to honor ancestors and departed loved ones.

As centuries passed, Samhain evolved and blended with other cultural and religious practices, especially after the spread of Christianity. This fusion gave rise to All Saints' Day and, eventually, the modern celebration of Halloween. Many customs enjoyed today – such as dressing up in costumes, carving pumpkins, and sharing stories of spirits and the supernatural – have roots in these ancient traditions.

Learn more about Samhain at the link in our bio.

Uncover a bread that connects the worlds of the living and the departed 🍞💀 

Pan de muerto, or “bread of the dead,” is a sweet Mexican bread baked for Día de los Muertos. This special bun is often decorated with bone-shaped designs and dusted with sugar, symbolizing the cycle of life and death.

Families across Mexico come together to bake and share pan de muerto, honoring their loved ones who have passed away. It is commonly placed on altars, known as ofrendas, alongside marigolds, candles, and photographs, serving as a tribute to ancestors.

Different regions add their unique touches to pan de muerto, incorporating various flavors and designs into the tradition. Some versions are infused with orange blossom water or anise seeds.

Visit the link in our bio to read about this delicious piece of Mexican heritage that sweetly unites the realms of the living and the dead.

🪔 Will you celebrate the “Festival of Lights” this year?

Diwali is one of the most significant festivals in Hindu and other Indian religions, celebrated by millions of people across the world. Its origins date back over 2,500 years.

Diwali is rooted in various ancient stories and legends that symbolize the victory of light over darkness, good over evil, and knowledge over ignorance.

In 2024, the festival will take place from 30 October to 3 November. The festival typically spans five days, each with its own meaning and rituals:

🌟Dhanteras: The first day is dedicated to prosperity. People clean their homes and purchase precious items like gold or new kitchen utensils, symbolizing good fortune.

✨Naraka Chaturdasi (Choti Diwali): On the second day, people wake up early to apply aromatic oils before bathing, believed to remove impurities and prepare for the festivities.

🪔Lakshmi Puja (Main Diwali): The third day is the main event. Families light diyas (oil lamps) and candles around their homes, perform puja (prayers) to goddess Lakshmi, and enjoy fireworks to ward off evil spirits.

🌧️Govardhan Puja: The fourth day commemorates Lord Krishna’s lifting of Govardhan Hill to protect villagers from torrential rains. People build small mounds of cow dung or clay, symbolizing the hill, and worship them.

🔥Bhai Dooj: The fifth and final day celebrates the bond between brothers and sisters. Sisters perform aarti (a ritual with light) for their brothers and pray for their well-being, while brothers give gifts in return.

We know that not everyone has the kind of relationship with their father that’s easily captured in a standard greeting card. 

If you’ve gone “no contact” or “low contact” with a parent to protect your mental health, we know that this requires courage. That’s why, if you have complex feelings about this holiday, we want you to know that you are seen, understood, and yes, celebrated.

To that end, we’d like to share with you a personal essay written by our very own Sam Dylan Finch. 

Sam’s experience as an LGBTQ+ adult who chose estrangement will likely resonate with any adult who has made the difficult decision to choose themselves, especially in a culture that emphasizes that family is everything.

Sam writes, “I know that the ways in which my parents couldn’t love me are only a reflection of the ways in which they couldn’t love themselves. That’s a deep suffering I’ve known, too — and while I cannot free my parents or anyone else from that pain, I can do everything within my power now to free myself.”

The journey to liberate oneself after trauma is lifelong, but we think Sam’s words offer a glimpse of what the path to self-love might look like. 

Head to our bio to read Sam’s essay and if you feel called to, leave a supportive comment for those who might be feeling alone on this holiday.

भूख लगने पर आजकल लोग बाहर से खाना ऑर्डर करते हैं. डिलिवरी बॉय आता है और खाना देकर चला जाता है. लेकिन दिल्ली में एक शख्स ने दावा किया कि उसने दिवाली से पहले बिरयानी मंगवाई तो डिलिवरी बॉय ने उसे डांट दिया. शख्स ने कहा कि जो शख्स उसकी बिरयानी का ऑर्डर लेकर आया था, उसने उसके खाने की चॉइस को लेकर सवाल खड़े कर दिए. 

इस शख्स ने ऑनलाइन सोशल मीडिया फ़ोरम पर अपनी कहानी बताई. उसने कहबा कि जैसे ही ऑर्डर रिसीव हुआ तो डिलिवरी एजेंट ने ओटीपी मांगा. कोड डालने के बाद डिलिवरी एजेंट गया नहीं बल्कि उसे डांटने लगा. उस डिलिवरी एजेंट ने कहा कि जो खाना उसने ऑर्डर किया है, वह गलत है. डिलिवरी एजेंट ने उससे कहा, 'ये बहुत गलत कर रहे हो आप, ठीक नहीं है ये.' 

डिलिवरी एजेंट की यह बात सुनकर वह शख्स हैरान रह गया और पूछा कि खाने में क्या गलत है. इस पर एजेंट ने कहा कि आपको दिवाली के बाद तक चिकन या मटन नहीं खाना चाहिए. त्योहारों के समय कुछ 'साफ' चीज खाइए.

शख्स ने कहा कि यह बात सुनकर मैं सकते में आ गया और मुझे समझ नहीं आया कि क्या बोलूं. शख्स ने कहा, 'मैं एक दोषी मुस्कान के साथ खड़ा रह गया, यार, क्या बोलता मैं उनको? आखिर उसे इसकी परवाह क्यों है? '

सीमा विवाद को लेकर नेपाल और भारत के साथ तनातनी लगातार जारी है. इसके साथ ही नेपाल और भारत के बीच सीमा से जुड़ा विवाद फिर गहराने वाला है. इसे एक बार फिर नेपाल की तरफ से बढ़ाया जा रहा है. नेपाल ने पहले तो अपने देश में नोट बदलने की बात की फिर भारत के तीन हिस्‍सों को लेकर विवादित नक्शे छापने शुरू किया और अब नोट छापने के लिए चीन की कंपनी से डील भी कर लिया है. जिससे दोनों देशों के बीच विवाद फिर बढ़ने के आसार हैं. 

नेपाल के केन्द्रीय बैंक ‘नेपाल राष्ट्र बैंक’ ने देश के संशोधित राजनीतिक मानचित्र वाले 100 रुपये के नए नोट छापने का ठेका एक चीनी कंपनी को दिया है. नेपाल के मंत्रिमंडल ने 100 रुपये के नोट के डिजाइन में बदलाव को मंजूरी दे दी है. इसमें रणनीतिक रूप से महत्वपूर्ण तीन क्षेत्रों लिंपियाधुरा, लिपुलेख और कालापानी को नेपाल का हिस्सा बताया गया है. नए राजनीतिक मानचित्र को 18 जून, 2020 को नेपाली संविधान में संशोधन कर मंजूरी दी गई थी जिसमें लिपुलेख, कालापानी और लिंपियाधुरा को देश के हिस्से के तौर पर दिखाया गया है.

वायु प्रदूषण को हल्के में लेने की गलती न करें, यह कोविड-19 से भी घातक साबित हो सकता है! AIIMS दिल्ली के पूर्व डायरेक्टर और अब मेदांता में इंटरनल मेडिसिन के चेयरमैन, डॉ रणदीप गुलेरिया ने यही चेतावनी दी थी. उन्होंने कहा था कि वायु प्रदूषण के कारण कोविड-19 से होने वाली मृत्यु दर की तुलना में मृत्यु दर अधिक हो सकती है. दिल्ली समेत NCR में AQI लगातार खराब हो रहा है. गुरुवार की रात तक एयर क्वालिटी और बिगड़ सकती है. केंद्रीय प्रदूषण नियंत्रण बोर्ड के अनुसार, गुरुवार सुबह आनंद विहार का AQI 418 है जो 'गंभीर' श्रेणी में है. IMD का पूर्वानुमान है कि गुरुवार को दिवाली की सुबह धुंध रहेगी लेकिन दिन में आसमान साफ रहेगा.

हिन्दू धर्म में दीपावली का त्योहार प्रमुख त्योहारों में से एक होता है. लोगों को इस पर्व का पूरे सालभर से इंतजार रहता है. जानकारी के लिए बता दें कि कार्तिक महीने के कृष्ण पक्षी की अमावस्या तिथि पर दिवाली मनाई जाती है. इस साल दिवाली कई जगहों पर आज यानी 31 अक्टूबर और कई जगहों पर कल यानी 1 नवंबर को मनाई जाएगी. इस दिन घर में साफ-सफाई का विशेष रूप से ध्यान रखा जाता है. दिवाली पर मां लक्ष्मी और गणेश जी की पूजा करने का विधान है. लक्ष्मी-गणेश जी की पूजा करने से घर में सुख-शांति का वास होता है और धन-धान्य की कमी नहीं होती है. 

वैदिक पंचांग के अनुसार कार्तिक महीने की अमावस्या तिथि की शुरुआत 31 अक्टूबर को 3 बजकर 52 मिनट पर होगी. वहीं, इसका समापन 1 नवंबर को शाम 6 बजकर 16 मिनट पर होगा. 

धार्मिक मान्यताओं के अनुसार दिवाली पर पूजा प्रदोष काल में की जाती है. ऐसे में प्रदोष काल का समय 31 अक्टूबर को शाम 5 बजकर 36 मिनट से लेकर रात 8 बजकर 11 मिनट तक रहेगा. इस दौरान लक्ष्मी पूजन किया जा सकता है.

A new Louisiana law, effective August 1, makes it illegal to stand within 25 feet of a police officer engaged in law enforcement duties after being ordered to stay back. ⁠

Supporters, including Gov. Jeff Landry and bill author Rep. Bryan Fontenot, argue it enhances officer safety. ⁠
⁠
While critics, including former Gov. John Bel Edwards and the ACLU of Louisiana, contend it infringes on citizens’ First Amendment rights to observe and hold police accountable. ⁠
⁠
Violating the law can result in a fine of up to $500, 60 days in jail, or both.

While I’m currently stranded in an airport after a strange, global outage that freaks me out if I think about it too deeply, the last week or so has been lovely. Met wonderful people. Visited a city I’d never been. Caught up with my dear friend. Enjoyed some nice new ORIGIN news. Launched a special. Plus… it’s summertime! Remember what Zora told us: “Jump at the sun. You might not land on it, but at least you’ll get off the ground.” 🌞

Last week, I returned to Paris for Art Basel to celebrate the landmark 28 women-directed short films commissioned by Miu Miu over the past decade+ through its tremendous “Miu Miu Women’s Tales.” Proud to have been Director #5 with THE DOOR, starring Gabrielle Union, back in 2013. And proud to convene with many of the wonderful lady directors thanks to Mrs. Prada, @veesback and team. Fantastic time. Important project. Bravo, Verde! Then, maestro @darrenwalker invited me to meet the great artist Barbara Chase-Riboud, who was being honored with an unprecedented eight-venue simultaneous exhibition saluting a half century of her exceptional work across sculpture and poetry. What an icon. Grateful to Darren, @thelmagolden and @mseringilbert for acquainting me with the work of this transformational artist in such a generous way. Been to Paris many times over the years, but this trip was my favorite by a landslide. Thanks to all who made it so. xo

The Academy Museum is a wondrous place for film lovers. On Saturday night, we raised funds for this beautiful institution, which celebrates and archives all things film. Thanks to my fellow Academy governors for their leadership. Thanks to @nicolasghesquiere and the whole @louisvuitton family, plus @katiebof, for always seeing me as I am and making me feel glamorous. Special shout to the one and only @indiamhammond who handled this hair and makeup alone in one hour and ten minutes! Thanks to my pals in this crazy industry who I got to embrace and laugh with and catch up with. Felt like a high school reunion of sorts. Consider visiting the Academy Museum when you can. It’s worth your time. xo

Forty-eight hours in Paris felt like a deep, cool breath of fresh air. Thank you @nicolasghesquiere and @louisvuitton for a gorgeous time celebrating your vivacious and vibrant Women’s SS25 Collection. I swooned!

Four nights in Morelia! A stunning city in Mexico, declared a UNESCO World Heritage Site for its gorgeous architecture. What a gem of a place. I was a guest of the outstanding Morelia Film Festival, and I have to say it was one of the top five festival experiences I’ve ever had. And I’ve attended dozens and dozens and dozens around the world over the years. Fantastic - from the films, filmmakers and audience to the ambience, spirit and intention. Grateful to @al_moreliano, Daniela and the team for treating me like family and presenting the Latin American premiere of ORIGIN with ARRAY - almost a year after the film’s distributor opened the picture without Mexico. Onward! ¡No puedo esperar a volver a Michoacán!

I got two incredibly meaningful awards this week 🥹 the @foundermade award for food innovation for our Cravings baking mixes, and the @girlscouts changemaker award. Both have left me in shambles this week as they encompass two major parts of entire life - my company, and being a mom. 

There was a time in my life where I never thought I would fit into this world ever again. I’m riddled with anxiety, worried I am never getting anything right. That I have ZERO clue what I am doing. So many things. But I feel so incredibly humbled by these awards, and they show me that while holy shit I still have no idea what I’m doing, I am doing *something* right. So this is for everyone who thinks the whole world has it together and you just don’t: no. None of us know what we are doing. We just do the best we can every day. For our companies, for our children, for our families, for ourselves. Just do the best you can. Every day that will look a little different, and that is ok. Love you all!!!

We can never be too early or too late to discover the passions within ourselves, allowing dreams of achievement to be renewed. As they say, it is true that age cannot dictate whether one finds a fulfilling job or achieves their purpose in life. 

I am here to tell you: if you are beginning a new career at forty or opening a new business at sixty, you bring much to the world. If your goal requires time, set a challenging target, map out your plan, and gather supportive people around you.

At Corporate Stalwarts, we get that feeling overwhelmed is pretty common in today's fast-paced world. Instead of letting burnout take control, we choose to support one another and build resilience.

Mindfulness, self-care, and genuine connections are at the core of what we do. 

We lift each other, creating a supportive space where everyone feels safe to share their feelings. Our mantra is simple: growth happens together.

As candidates striving for growth and success, it’s easy to get caught up in immediate results. However, true progress and accomplishment stem from the consistent actions and decisions we make regularly. 

Every effort, no matter how small, contributes to the broader journey toward your personal and professional goals. Planting seeds represents dedication to learning, improving, and taking initiative. 

It's about focusing on what you can control—your actions and attitude—rather than fixating solely on the outcome. 

Remember, the harvest will come with time and persistence, but it can't exist without today's seeds. 

By embracing this mindset, candidates cultivate a more resilient and forward-thinking approach to realizing their potential. 

Key Takeaways: 

• Focus on consistent actions 
• Value small efforts 
• Control your actions and attitude 
• Embrace learning and improvement 
• Be patient for the results

No matter what, Joan Rivers could always make us laugh! Tomorrow, we will be celebrating our dear friend and longtime supporter at Dead Funny - An All-Star Tribute to Joan Rivers benefiting God’s Love We Deliver 💖

We spotted Executive Producer @melissariversofficial on @newyorklivetv talking about how much God's Love meant to herself and Joan. We are grateful to work with Melissa to bring everyone together for an unforgettable evening!

Limited tickets are still available, visit the link in our bio! 🎟

#JoanRivers #JoanIsDeadFunny

⭐ Hey now, we love you all-stars! ⭐ The biggest names in comedy came out last night to the @ApolloTheater to for Dead Funny -- An All-Star Tribute to @JoanRivers, benefiting God's Love We Deliver. This unforgettable event launched the 20th annual @NYComedyFestival and in case you couldn't make it, you're in for a treat because the event will air soon on NBCUniversal!

Thank you to @RachelBrosnahan, @MichelleButeau, @SandraBernhard, @NikkiGlaser, tiffanyhaddish, @ChelseaHandler, @MatteoLane, @JoelMcHale, @PattonOswalt, @AubreyPlaza, @RandyRainbow, @JeffRoss and RitaWilson for sharing your personal memories of and tributes to Joan, who we know is forever in all of our hearts.

Thank you to Executive Producers @MelissaRivers, @ErichBergen, David Jammy, and Chris Convy, and to @WhoopiGoldberg for co-chairing the night.

Joan was the real deal for God's Love. We began at the height of the AIDS pandemic, a time of great stigma and fear. One person who was not afraid was Joan Rivers. As a God’s Love Board member, Joan was one of the first public figures to offer their support. She threw the weight of her celebrity, her heart and her pocketbook behind us.
 
Whether Joan was delivering meals on Thanksgiving Day or cheering on runners at our #RaceToDeliver, she did everything for God’s Love wholeheartedly.
 
Joan would be very proud of what God’s Love has become. This year, we will cook and deliver 5 million nutritious meals for people living with more than 200 different diagnoses. We remain the ONLY non-profit in NYC providing FREE medically tailored meals & nutrition services to people affected by severe illness, their families and caregivers. For so many, we are the only game in town.
 
Joan brought a face to the work we do, the people we serve, and our commitment to the idea that everyone who needs medically tailored meals has access to them.
 
We also thank Sam & Dena Lombardo, @CraigNewmark, @NYComedyFestival, @doneanddustedtv, @nbc, @take9, Barry Feirstein, Karen & Robert Kelly, Sunny Sessa, @apollotheater for helping make #JoanRiversIsDeadFunny possible.

This one-night-only event celebrating comedy icon and beloved God’s Love supporter, Joan Rivers, will take place on November 7th at The Apollo in New York City.

“Dead Funny - An All-Star Tribute to Joan Rivers benefiting God’s Love We Deliver” will also be the official opening night event of the 20th Annual New York Comedy Festival.

Joan Rivers was more than just a beloved friend to God’s Love — she was family. For more than 25 years, Joan was a steadfast supporter of our mission, and she served as a member of our Board of Directors for two decades. Her commitment to our work was unwavering, and we are honored to pay tribute to her remarkable legacy through this special event, which has been 10 years in the making.

As parents, we strive to give our kids the best education, opportunities, and experiences. 

But have you ever thought about the simplest yet most powerful foundation for their health and happiness?

One of them is sleep.💤

Kids, just like adults, need quality sleep to thrive. But here’s the truth – our own habits often influence their sleep more than we realize.

In Megha’s story, a few simple adjustments led to huge improvements. It was about prioritizing the basics and setting the right example.✅

Swipe through to learn more about the importance of creating a healthy sleep routine to transform your child’s well-being, and why parents and family habits play a crucial role.👨‍👩‍👦‍👦

✨ What changes have you made in your routine as parents to promote healthier sleep habits for your kids? 
Share your thoughts in the comments below!

#SleepDeeperIndia #sleepforkids

✨ Motivation fades, but inspiration lasts. ✨

Ever wake up feeling like you have to work out, eat right, or meditate, but the struggle is real? 💪 

What if it wasn’t about forcing motivation, but falling in love with how these things make you feel? 🧘‍♀️💫

After a workout, pause. Soak up that energy boost. ⚡️ 
After a restful night, feel the morning freshness. 🌅 
Whether it’s a nourishing meal 🥗, a calming meditation 🧘, or a sunset 🌇, those feelings remind us why we do what we do. ❤️

The more we connect to these moments, the easier it becomes to keep showing up. ✨

Sometimes, all we need is to remember the feeling. 💭

#InspirationOverMotivation #MindfulLiving #WellnessJourney #HealthyHabits #MindsetShift #FindYourWhy #StayInspired #PauseReflectReconnect #SelfLoveJourney #Wellbeing

lifestyle is everything …it includes where you eat , how much you eat , what time you eat , quality of choices, your movement , sleep , emotions and mainly your attitude and mindset …..it’s working with root causes rather than just symptoms it also involves you living your authentic self and not trying to be someone else 

If age was the problem everyone would have the same outcome of disease , difficult menopause , prostate issues , weak bones , wasting muscle , low libido , but that ain’t the truth ….wake up India 🇮🇳 

#gethealthyindia #holistichealth

it’s not always about more microbiome testing , probiotics and  complex gut cleanses ….many times it’s back to basics ….

#guthealth #guthealthmatters #gethealthyindia #holistichealth #lukecoutinho @youcarelifestyle

A young pharmacist came to us with painful varicose veins, worsened by long hours ⏰ on her feet & compounded by PCOS. She faced severe leg pain, especially around her menstrual cycle, heavy bleeding, weight gain, low energy & disrupted sleep—all impacting her ability to function at work & in daily life. ♨️

Her history of depression also meant we needed to prioritize her emotional health.

In Integrative & Lifestyle Medicine, we understand that symptoms rarely exist in isolation. Our team mapped🔍 her unique lifestyle factors & health history to uncover the interconnected causes of her discomfort, enabling us to build a scientifically designed, root-cause-based plan.

Rather than focusing solely on symptom relief, we took a holistic approach to improve her circulatory health, hormonal balance & inflammation. While compression socks 🧦 & pain medications 💊 were on, true healing required addressing deeper, underlying issues—where integrative & lifestyle medicine became key to a long-term healing plan. 

Our integrative strategy included:

⚖️Cellular nutrition to support angiogenesis, DNA repair, stem cell regeneration, immune health, gut microbiome balance & reduced inflammation.
✔️Hormone balancing protocol to stabilize estrogen-progesterone
🚶‍♀️Foundational movements, strength training & yoga to build lean muscle, improve circulation & reduce body fat.
🔻Reducing estrogen dominance
🍏Fixing key micronutrient deficiencies
🧹Lymphatic health practices to enhance circulation & elimination 
🧘‍♂️Meditation, breathwork & mindfulness practices to build emotional resilience
🌞Circadian medicine 

With each element addressed, she saw remarkable changes: reduced PMS, less leg pain & heaviness, visible improvement in her varicose veins & higher energy levels. As her body fat % dropped & lean muscle increased, her hormonal balance & menstrual health improved too.✔️

Many people are told to “live with” their conditions, but this isn’t always the answer. While medications can provide relief, true healing is possible when we address the root causes through lifestyle changes & the right attitude.🙌🏻

We help you find a way🤝
.

#varicosevein #pcod #lifestylemedicine

this high-protein buffalo chicken dip is creamy, satisfying, and perfect for football Sundays 🏈 full recipe below:

🖤 ingredients
1 cup siggi’s 0% plain skyr
1/2 cup cottage cheese
1 cup shredded cheddar cheese
1/2 cup buffalo sauce
1 egg
1 cup shredded chicken
1/2 tsp garlic powder
1/2 tsp ground pepper
ranch and chopped chopped green onions for topping

🖤 directions
preheat your oven to 400 degrees. 
add everything but the ranch and green onion to a mixing bowl. mix well. 
spray a 9x9 baking dish with avocado oil and spoon the buffalo chicken dip mix into the dish. 
cover with foil and bake for 30 minutes. remove the foil, turn the oven to broil and put the dip back in the oven for another 5 minutes, or until the top is crispy. 
serve with celery sticks and blue corn tortilla chips.

Danielle Deadwyler was not expecting to cry. The actor, who won accolades in 2022 for her heartbreaking performance as civil rights advocate Mamie Till-Mobley in “Till,” was describing the emotional journey of her latest project, “The Piano Lesson,” when she suddenly leaned sideways in her chair, twisting her neck at an awkward angle.

“I don’t want to mess up my makeup,” said @danielledeadwyler, wiping away tears as she spoke about the film’s acknowledgment of the pain and trauma endured by its characters, descendants of slaves living in Depression-era Pittsburgh. “The whole making of this thing, there’s a tension riding. For me, it’s because of the huge weight of Black families that’s been put on our shoulders in a certain kind of way.”

Deadwyler is not alone in being moved by @thepianolessonfilm_, which begins its limited theatrical run Friday before landing on Netflix on Nov. 22. Many critics have already given high marks to the latest in the platform’s series of screen adaptations of August Wilson’s “Century Cycle” of plays, which spotlight the triumphs and hardships faced by Black Americans in the 20th century, decade by decade.

Produced by Denzel Washington and Todd Black and featuring Washington’s son John David Washington (“Black KkKlansman”), Samuel L. Jackson (“Pulp Fiction”) and Corey Hawkins (“In The Heights”) among its cast, “The Piano Lesson’s” credits are full of bold-faced names. But it’s Deadwyler who’s been singled out for her take-no-prisoners portrayal of Berniece, a single mother locked in a tense and potentially violent battle with her brother Boy Willie (Washington) over the family’s heirloom piano, decorated with the haunting carvings of their enslaved ancestors.

The forensic analysis of Donald Trump's political comeback began as soon as he was declared the winner, and a popular take quickly emerged: Trump’s win could be attributed, at least in part, to all of his podcast appearances. In the lead-up to Election Day, Trump went on a slew of massively popular podcasts catering to right-leaning young male audiences. That demographic, white men ages 18 to 29, wound up voting for Trump by a 28-point margin. As it turns out, the mastermind behind this plan might have been Trump’s 18-year-old son, Barron. It was inspired by a small horological mechanism that regulates mainspring tension, ensuring accuracy. What better way to embody Vacheron Constantin’s pursuit of precision and quality?
 
Excellence perpetuates excellence…

✠ More than a logo
 
Immediately recognisable, the Maltese Cross continues to inspire the Maison today. You’ll find it in every detail: fixed bezel, tourbillon, lugs, bracelet links. Can you think of a timepiece that features it?
 
A story is in the making...

✠ The Maltese Cross
 
1880: the Maison officially chooses the Maltese cross as its emblem. But what is the story behind it? Discover that part tomorrow.
